   "author_association" : "MEMBER",
   "body" : "Instead of automatically creating and loading a default wallet, users should instead explicitly create their wallet or load it on start.\r\n\r\nThis PR is built on #15450 to allow users to create wallets in the GUI.\r\n\r\nTo make the UX better, we also should reload the wallets that were loaded on the last close. So this also uses #11082 to write the loaded wallets to the `bitcoin_rw.conf` file on close and then loads those wallets again on the next start. \r\n\r\nThe issue described in #15453 is very prominent here because the default behavior is the same as starting with `-nowallet` right now.",
